  <p>Block 2 covers the four erosion agents — water (rivers, sheet, wave), wind, ice, and gravity (mass wasting) — and where each dominates and why. Worked example: trace erosion processes in a Marina Beach satellite sequence (2005, 2015, 2025) and ask "what's moving where?" Student work: each student picks one erosion process and finds a Chennai-area example using Google Earth, then does a 2-minute share-out. Connect-forward to Block 3's river focus.</p>
